pageContext.claim: “AOC+3, I don't think she ever went, I don't think, I don't, did, she went to a college, right? Did she ever take an environmental course? All of a sudden she's saying "No more cars, no more planes, no more flying.”
pageContext.analysis: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez (D-N.Y.), who graduated cum laude from Boston University, did not say "no more cars, no more planes, no more flying" when she introduced the nonbinding environmental resolution known as the Green New Deal.
